Topic.Title: Lucid observation

Message.Msg: Here is all of the data So how do trade a breakout? If you are looking to get long GOOG the way to take advantage of this move is to wait for the stock to breakout out and clear old highs and then wait for what happens next. Either the breakout will fail right at old highs or the stock will clear old highs only to be hit back down by those who fade breakouts. A stock hitting new high territory is a good sign but its what happens after the breakout that tells you if a run in GOOG will happen in the next couple of weeks. We would look to get long GOOG if 1 of the following 2 things happen: #1 If the breakout hits new highs but fails, pulls back above the old highs level and starts building a base. #2 If the breakout fails and is smacked down all the way back into its base but above the $638-$648 level. This is the level of the last consolidation and can act as support before the 2nd rally attempt occurs. The most favorable of the 2 setups is the #1 scenario where a pullback with at least 2 days will get us looking for a confirmation pattern and can allow us to get in at a very favorable price ahead of a potential big rally into new high territory.

Message.Msg: Judge in Google-Oracle case seeks names of paid reporters, bloggers By Alexei Oreskovic SAN FRANCISCO | Wed Aug 8, 2012 12:13pm EDT SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) - A judge in the patent battle between Google Inc and Oracle Corp ordered the companies to disclose the names of journalists on their payrolls, stunning the legal and media communities. The highly unusual order was issued on Tuesday by U.S. District Judge William Alsup, who said he was concerned that Google and Oracle or their counsel had retained or paid people who may have published comment on the case. The order, issued several months after a jury found that Google did not infringe Oracle patents, hints at the possibility of a hidden world of for-pay press coverage and injects uncertainty into the widely followed case.
